column13: The utility model relates to a spraying bird feeder which comprises a body and a cover plate assembled in the body. The positions of the cover plate and the body are lower than the top end of the body; a containing space used for containing water is formed between the cover plate and the body, and a sprayer is arranged in the containing space. And the cover plate is provided with a water injectionnozzle corresponding to the mounting position of the sprayer. According to the utility model, the cover plate is used for providing a standing position for birds, the birds can stand on the cover plate to drink water on the cover plate, and the water quantity on the cover plate cannot threaten the life safety of the birds, so that the safety of the birds during water drinking is improved.

column13: The utility model discloses a wind bell. The device comprises a hanging piece, a connecting piece hung below the hanging piece, an impacting piece hung below the connecting piece, a plurality of windbell pipes, a plurality of first hanging ropes connected between the hanging piece and the connecting piece, and a plurality of second hanging ropes connected between the connecting piece and the impacting piece, wherein the third hanging ropes are connected between the connecting piece and the wind bell pipe and correspond to the wind bell pipe one by one, the battery box is arranged on the connecting piece, the LED lamp strings are arranged on the second hanging ropes or the third hanging ropes and electrically connected with the battery box, and the partition layers wrap the periphery of the impact piece. According to the utility model, the interlayer is sleeved on the periphery of the impact piece, and the tone of the impact piece impacted by the wind bell tube can be changed through the number change of the interlayer, so that the requirements of different users are met; and the LED lamp strings are arranged, so that the LED lamp has a light-emitting effect, and the decorative property is improved.

column12: Flame assisting structure of flame handicraft
column13: The utility model discloses a flame assisting structure of a flame handicraft. The flame assisting structure comprises a base, a fire source container placed in a furnace chamber of the base, and a diffuser which covers the upper end of the furnace chamber, wherein the fire source container is used for containing fuel, an air guide sleeve which is adapted to the furnace chamber is also arranged in the furnace chamber of the base, the fire source container is placed in the guide sleeve, at least two spiral convex ribs are arranged on the outer wall of the guide sleeve along the axial direction, and a spiral airway which extends from the bottom of the base to the upper end of the base is formed between the spiral convex ribs and the inner wall of the furnace chamber. When a combustible material placed in the fire source container is lit and burnt, air is absorbed into the furnace chamber from the bottom of the base, spirally flows out from the upper end of the furnace chamber along the spiral airway formed between the convex ribs of the guide sleeve and the furnace chamber, and contacts with open fire of a fire source, and spiral airflow can drive flame of the open fire to rotate and move upwards so as to realize the flame handicraft which can be used for enlarging and heightening the flame and improving the attractiveness of the flame.
column15: STEPHEN DELL PORTER

column12: Container house with beer making equipment
column13: The utility model discloses a container house with beer making equipment. The container house comprises a container, a mounting frame, a filter tank, a fermentation tank, an ethylene glycol tank, a cooling container, a refrigerating machine and a heat exchange system, the mounting frame is fixedly mounted in the container, the filter tank, the fermentation tank, the ethylene glycol and the heat exchange system are all mounted on a working table of the mounting frame and arranged in the container, the cooling container is mounted below the working table of the mounting frame and located under the fermentation tank, and the refrigerating machine is mounted in the container. Due to the fact that the filter tank, the fermentation tank, the ethylene glycol tank, the cooling container, the refrigerating machine, the heat exchange system and the like are installed in the container in a centralized mode, the size is small, beer making equipment can be conveniently transported to any place through the trailer, the trailer passes through electric power, and the beer making equipment has the advantage of being convenient to move. In addition, the cooling container is arranged under the fermentation tank, so that the prepared beer can be quickly stored in the cooling container, and the beer fermentation device is very convenient to use.

column12: Furnace capable of being quickly assembled and disassembled
column13: The utility model discloses a stove capable of being quickly assembled and disassembled. The stove comprises a table plate, stand columns, side plates and limiting pieces, a through hole is formed in the middle of the table board, and connecting parts corresponding to the stand columns are arranged on the lower surface of the table board; the upper end face of the stand column is connected with the connecting part through a rotary buckle, and a mounting groove is formed in the side face of the stand column and extends downwards in the axis direction of the stand column to penetrate through the lower end face of the stand column. Two ends of the side plate are respectively mounted on the mounting grooves of the two upright posts, and the end parts of the side plate are upwards embedded into the mounting grooves from the lower ends of the upright posts; the limiting pieces are movably connected to the lower ends of the side faces of the stand columns and used for limiting the side plates and preventing the side plates from disengaging from the mounting grooves. According to the utility model, all the parts of the stove are assembled in a movable connection manner and are independent from one another, so that the stove occupies a small space after being disassembled, is convenient to transport and saves the storage cost; the table plate is connected with the stand column through the rotary buckle, the stand column is connected with the side plate through the inserting groove, the side plate is positioned through the limiting piece, screws are not needed for fixing, dismounting and mounting are convenient, and efficiency is high.

column13: The utility model discloses a wind bell structure which comprises a hooking piece, a connecting assembly hung below the hooking piece, a wind bell disc assembly hung below the connecting assembly, a plurality of adjustable hanging assemblies connected to the connecting assembly and a plurality of wind bell pipes hung on the hanging assemblies and surrounding the wind bell disc assembly. The hanging ropes are used for hanging; the wind bell disc assembly comprises a wind bell disc and a plurality of rod pieces, the rod pieces are arranged in the radial direction of the wind bell disc and inserted into the periphery of the wind bell disc at equal-angle intervals, and the wind bell pipes are matched among the rod pieces respectively to achieve separation. The rod pieces are arranged on the periphery of the wind bell disc to separate the wind bell tubes, the rhythm is changed through collision of the wind bell tubes and the wind bell disc or the rod pieces, mutual collision of the wind bell tubes is avoided, and the protection effect is achieved. During use, the melody can be changed by changing the material of the rod piece, so that diversified market demands are met; the position of the wind bell pipe can be adjusted through the suspension assembly to change the rhythm.

column13: The utility model discloses a novel wind bell which comprises a plurality of hanging ropes, hanging pieces connected to the upper ends of the hanging ropes, connecting pieces movably matched with themiddles of the hanging ropes, a wind bell disc connected to the lower ends of the hanging ropes and a plurality of wind bell pipes. Wherein strip-shaped holes in one-to-one correspondence with the hanging ropes are formed in the connecting piece, a plurality of positioning grooves are formed in the strip-shaped holes in the axial direction, and the strip-shaped holes are distributed at equal intervals in the circumferential direction of the connecting piece with the center of the connecting piece as the circle center. The middle part of the hanging rope is arranged in the strip-shaped hole ina penetrating manner and is matched in one positioning groove; and the wind bell pipes are in one-to-one correspondence with the hanging ropes and are arranged around the wind bell disc. column12: Thermal insulation device for flame artware
column13: The utility model discloses a thermal insulation device for a flame artware. The flame artware comprises a base, a fire source container placed in a furnace chamber of the base, and a light transmittable cover covered at the upper end of the furnace chamber; fuel is contained in the fire source container; the light transmittable cover consists of an inner cover and an outer cover; and an air gap is formed between the inner cover and the outer cover. According to the thermal insulation device for the flame artware, a double-layer light transmittable cove is arranged, and a gap is formed between the inner cover and the outer cover of the light transmittable, which can insulate part of the heat on the inner cover to realize a great thermal insulation function; and another gap is formed between the lower end of the outer cover and the base, so that the gap between the inner cover and the outer cover can form the air gap for ventilating, and as a result, the radiating function of the inner cover is improved, the thermal insulation function of the light transmittable cover is further improved, and the safety of the flame artware in use is ensured.
column15: STEPHEN DELL PORTER

column13: A biomass fuel furnace relates to combustion equipment and comprises a furnace body, a furnace pipe and a furnace table, wherein the side wall of the furnace pipe comprises an inner layer and an outer layer, plural air exhaust holes are disposed in the outer layer, plural air ducts extended and disposed from bottom to top are disposed between the inner layer and the outer layer, and the air exhaust holes are upper ports of the air ducts; and the outer surface of the outer layer is winded by a heating pipe. The biomass fuel furnace provided by the invention has the beneficial effect that when wind enters the furnace body, one part of the wind directly enters the furnace pipe to realize sustained combustion of fuels; and the other part of wind enters the air ducts and then flees from the air exhaust holes into the middle upper part of the furnace pipe. When the wind in the air ducts flees into the furnace pipe, flame gets close to the center shaft of the furnace pipe and is avoided from running around. After multiple air flows gather inside the furnace pipe, wind speed above the furnace pipe increases, air mobility in the fuel furnace is ensured, and the fuels can be completely burnt; and heat of the side wall of the furnace pipe is used to heat a water flow in the heating pipe so as to add functions of the fuel furnace and increase utilization rate of the heat.

column12: VERFAHREN ZUR VERBRENNUNG VON SCHWEFELHALTIGEN KOHLENSTOFFMATERIALIEN
column13: In a process for burning a combustible, sulfur-containing carbonaceous material such as coal, municipal waste, or tires, recrystallized metamorphic CaCO3 is introduced into the combustion zone along with the fuel. The amount of SO2 and NO2 generated is substantially reduced as compared to conventional processes and, even with no post-scrubbing equipment, the emission levels compare favorably to the emission levels of state-of-the-art power plants using the same coal with extensive emission controls. The present process also acts to convert sulfur resident in coal into elemental sulfur and loose sulfur compounds and to reduce the particulate output.

column12: SYSTEMS AND METHODS FOR COMMUNICATION CHANNEL CAPACITY CHANGE DETECTION
column13: Systems and methods for communication channel capacity detection are provided. One method includes monitoring a bandwidth over time of a channel communicatively coupling a plurality of medical devices at a first location with a second location remote from the first location and determining when a channel bandwidth of the channel exceeds a defined threshold value using the monitored bandwidth. The method also includes transmitting control signals from the second location to the plurality of devices at the first location to adjust a transmission rate of medical data from the plurality of medical devices to the second location and limiting a rate of transmission of the control signals to the plurality of medical devices based on a probability that the transmission of the control signals causes the channel bandwidth to exceed the defined threshold value.

column12: MONITORING CABLES AND METHODS FOR MONITORING RAIL TRACKS
column13: A monitoring cable includes an outer jacket having a generally rectangular cross-sectional profile. The monitoring cable further includes a strain monitoring unit disposed within the outer jacket, the strain monitoring unit including a plurality of optical fibers embedded in a potting layer. The monitoring cable further comprises a protective unit disposed within the outer jacket and spaced from the strain monitoring unit, the protective unit including an optical fiber disposed within a metal outer jacket. A method for monitoring a rail track includes attaching a monitoring cable to the rail track. The method further includes monitoring strain of the rail track by measuring movement of the optical fibers of the strain monitoring unit.

column12: Methods of processing data captured during a deposit transaction conducted at an image-based self-service check depositing terminal
column13: A method is provided of operating a self-service check depositing terminal. The method comprises the steps of receiving a user identification (ID) card from a depositor at the self-service check depositing terminal, reading ID data from the user ID card, sending the ID data to a consolidation server of a first financial institution to allow the first financial institution to process the ID data, and receiving from the first financial institution a first message containing a first Uniform Resource Locator (URL) which (i) is associated with a consolidation server of a second financial institution which is different from the first financial institution and (ii) is based upon the ID data which has been processed at the first financial institution.

column13: A power extraction system is provided and includes a low-pressure spool of a gas turbine engine, the low-pressure spool being rotatable at an input rotational speed between a first minimum speed and a first maximum speed, downstream components rotatable at an output rotational speed between a second minimum speed and a second maximum speed and a transmission assembly by which rotations of the low-pressure spool at the input rotational speed are transmittable at the output rotational speed to the downstream components. column13: The invention relates to a hinge for a vehicle door, comprising a first hinge part that can be fixed to the door or the door frame, a second hinge part which is fixed to the other of the two components, i.e. the door frame or the door, and a hinge pin that defines a swiveling axis of the hinge and pivotally connects the first hinge part and the second hinge part to each other. The hinge pin is arranged nonrotably on the first hinge part or the second hinge part while being rotatably mounted in the other hinge part. The hinge further comprises an end stop which limits an opening movement of the first hinge part and the second hinge part. In order to create a hinge that allows the vehicle door to be opened securely, an adjusting mechanism which is assigned to the first hinge part or the second hinge part is provided for adjusting the end stop.

column12: SYSTEM AND METHOD FOR ENHANCING DATA COMPRESSION USING DYNAMIC LEARNING AND CONTROL
column13: A data compression system and method for achieving enhanced compression performance in a plurality of encoder-decoder pairs communicatively coupled in a concatenated chain is disclosed. The plurality of encoder-decoder pairs receive input data and transform the input data into compressed output data. The data compression system includes at least one quality estimator communicatively coupled to the concatenated chain to determine a plurality of quality metrics corresponding to an output from each of the plurality of encoder-decoder pairs. Further, the data compression system also includes a processing subsystem configured to optimize the operation of each of the plurality of encoder-decoder pairs based upon the plurality of quality metrics to achieve a desired level of optimization for the concatenated chain.

column12: Hinged Door System for Attachment to a Display Unit
column13: There is provided a magnetically held hinged door for a display unit. The magnetically held hinged door includes a top plastic extruded component having three parts; a flange portion having one or more magnets adapted to removably attach the hinged door to metal shelves and other metal parts of the display unit; a retaining portion comprising an inverted U-shaped channel and a plurality of gripping tabs disposed in the inverted U-shaped channel; and a flexible hinge interconnecting the flange portion and the retaining portion. The magnetically held hinged door also includes a panel having an upper end removably retained within the inverted U-shaped channel. The magnetically held hinged door swings about the flexible hinge between a first closed position and a second open position.
column15: DELL UNTO BRUNO;;MYSKA STEPHEN;;GRADY GEORGE;;BEDER PHILIP;;KATZ DAVIT

column12: Seal structures for solid oxide fuel cell devices
column13: Disclosed are seals and seal structures for use in electrochemical devices such as solid oxide fuel cell devices. Exemplary seal structures are configured such that at least a portion of the interface between the seal and electrolyte sheet deviates from planarity by extending either (i) upwardly and inwardly (ii) or downwardly and inwardly, toward the active portion of the electrolyte sheet surface where one or more device electrodes are deposited. By angling the seal portion of the electrolyte sheet, the sharpness of any resulting bends or deformations that may occur during use can be reduced, thus reducing the likelihood of any cracks forming in the typically high stress regions of the electrolyte sheet. Further, preferably at least a portion of the electrolyte sheet contacting the seal composition, the seal - electrolyte interface may deviate from planarity by at least 0.1 mm from the seal - electrolyte interface, where the deviation from planarity extends normal to the seal or inwardly toward the active surface region of the electrolyte sheet. Also disclosed are methods for manufacturing the inventive seal structures and electrochemical device assemblies comprising same.
column15: DALE KETCHAM THOMAS;;STEPHEN ROSETTIE JOHN;;JOSEPH ST JULIEN DELL;;SUJANTO WIDJAJA

column12: NOVEL ANTIBODY AND USE IN DIAGNOSIS AND THERAPY OF ARTHROPATHIES
column13: The present invention provides a composition comprising an antibody or fragment thereof against oxidised Collagen II (CII) in which the antibody or fragment thereof is conjugated to a pharmaceutically active moiety. The invention also provides a composition comprising an antibody or fragment thereof against oxidised Collagen II (Gil) and a detectable label. The invention further provides the use of such compositions in medicine, in particular for the treatment of an arthropathy, and in methods of diagnosis.

column12: SYSTEMS AND METHODS FOR PROVIDING ULTRASOUND PROBE LOCATION AND IMAGE INFORMATION
column13: Systems and methods for providing ultrasound probe location and image information are provided. One system includes an ultrasound device coupled with an ultrasound probe and configured to acquire ultrasound images of a subject. The system further includes at least one of a plurality of digital cameras or a plurality of digital scanners configured to acquire scene information including images of the ultrasound probe with the subject during an image scan. The system also includes a processor having an ultrasound registration unit (URU) with the URU configured to identify and reference a probe location of the ultrasound probe to a surface of the object from the scene information and correlate the probe location to one or more of the acquired ultrasound images. The URU is additionally configured to generate a representation of the surface showing the identified and referenced probe location corresponding to the correlated ultrasound images.

column12: System, method, and computer software code for detecting a computer network intrusion in an infrastructure element of a high value target
column13: An intrusion detection system for detecting and defeating unauthorized intrusion within a computer network of an infrastructure element of a high value target, the system including a pre-processor configured to receive data from a computer network of an infrastructure element of a high value target and to output filtered data, a grammar applicator configured to apply grammars produced using a grammar based compression and learning algorithm to the filtered data, a decision making device configured to provide a recommendation based on an input from the grammar applicator as to whether the data in the computer network constitutes an unauthorized intrusion, and an emulator in communication with the decision making device configured to expand a sampling of the filtered data using a polymorphic transformation to allow the decision making device to further analyze the sampled data to determine an unauthorized intrusion. A method and a computer software code are also disclosed.

column12: Systems and methods for communicating ultrasound data
column13: Systems and methods for communicating ultrasound data are provided. One method includes monitoring over time estimates of bandwidth of a channel communicatively coupling an imaging location with another location remote from the imaging location and communicating the estimates to a system at the imaging location. The method also includes identifying at least one of a region-of-interest (ROI) mask or one or more transmission parameters for the channel and adjusting at least one of the ROI mask or the one or more transmission parameters based on the monitored estimates of the bandwidth for communicating the medical images.

column12: HEAT EXCHANGE AND TEMPERATURE SENSING DEVICE AND METHOD OF USE
column13: A method and apparatus are disclosed for preventing injury to an esophagus caused by heat or cold being delivered to the left atrium, the method including altering a heat exchange device from an insertable configuration to a heat exchanging configuration which has an inflated generally flattened cross section (e.g. capsule-shaped, elliptical) corresponding with the cross section of the inside of the esophagus such that the esophagus is maintained in its natural shape and location. In some embodiments the heat exchange device has a heat exchanger which is inflated to be in the heat exchanging configuration.
